( Alzheimer's disease (AD) is a form of dementia with a gradual memory loss and a progressive decline in mental functions with time (1, 2). It is characterized pathologically by neuronal loss, extracellular amyloid-beta senile plaques (APs aggregates of amyloid-beta peptides consisting of 40 to 42 amino acids) and intracellular neurofibrillary tangles (NFTs